1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:01,960
<i>Hello, dude.</i>

2
00:00:02,043 --> 00:00:03,962
<i>Dad found your brother's location.</i>

3
00:00:04,045 --> 00:00:05,922
<i>They're going to kill your brother.</i>

4
00:00:07,590 --> 00:00:09,175
<i>I was sleepwalking?</i>

5
00:00:09,259 --> 00:00:12,011
<i>You went down</i>
<i>the stairs and sat in the corner.</i>

6
00:00:12,095 --> 00:00:13,346
<i>What did I say?</i>

7
00:00:13,430 --> 00:00:15,682
<i>He's coming. He's already outside.</i>

8
00:00:15,765 --> 00:00:19,394
<i>I forgot to tell you.</i>
<i>Angelo is on his way home.</i>

9
00:00:19,477 --> 00:00:21,354
<i>Can we not talk about Edong for now?</i>

10
00:00:21,438 --> 00:00:22,772
<i>Lemuel.</i>

11
00:00:22,856 --> 00:00:25,191
<i>You told me</i>
<i>that Louisa was leaving Amurao.</i>

12
00:00:25,275 --> 00:00:27,485
<i>Did she ever mention</i>
<i>the word "bana" to you?</i>

13
00:00:27,569 --> 00:00:29,446
<i>My father is coming home.</i>

14
00:00:29,529 --> 00:00:30,655
<i>I'm in full family mode now.</i>

15
00:00:30,739 --> 00:00:32,198
<i>What a lunatic.</i>

16
00:00:34,617 --> 00:00:35,702
<i>Aah!</i>

17
00:00:36,745 --> 00:00:38,788
[laughs]

18
00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:46,546
[theme music playing]

19
00:01:56,074 --> 00:01:57,408
[tense music playing]

20
00:01:57,492 --> 00:01:58,159
[gunshots]

21
00:01:59,494 --> 00:02:02,080
[grunting]

22
00:02:02,163 --> 00:02:03,039
[blows land]

23
00:02:04,332 --> 00:02:06,835
- [Lucas grunting]
- [music becomes suspenseful]

24
00:02:06,918 --> 00:02:08,753
[both grunting]

25
00:02:08,837 --> 00:02:10,130
Ugh!

26
00:02:10,213 --> 00:02:12,298
[grunting]

27
00:02:12,382 --> 00:02:14,217
[grunts]

28
00:02:15,093 --> 00:02:20,348
- [suspenseful music continues]
- [groaning]

29
00:02:21,307 --> 00:02:23,560
[Lucas grunting]

30
00:02:24,769 --> 00:02:26,104
- Aah!
- [thud]

31
00:02:27,564 --> 00:02:29,190
[Lucas grunts]

32
00:02:30,733 --> 00:02:31,901
[tense music resumes]

33
00:02:31,985 --> 00:02:33,278
Where is Santiago?

34
00:02:34,988 --> 00:02:35,822
Come on!

35
00:02:36,698 --> 00:02:38,825
- [grunting]
- [blows landing]

36
00:02:38,908 --> 00:02:40,785
[both grunting]

37
00:02:40,869 --> 00:02:43,872
- [grunting]
- [Edong breathing heavily]

38
00:02:45,206 --> 00:02:46,541
- [Edong] Ah!
- [groans]

39
00:02:46,624 --> 00:02:47,542
[body thuds]

40
00:02:48,376 --> 00:02:49,836
Edong, run!

41
00:02:49,919 --> 00:02:50,795
Save yourself!

42
00:02:51,504 --> 00:02:53,339
If you let your brother escape,

43
00:02:53,423 --> 00:02:55,216
Boss will not be happy!

44
00:02:58,011 --> 00:02:59,512
Santiago!

45
00:02:59,596 --> 00:03:01,222
Run, Edong!

46
00:03:01,890 --> 00:03:03,099
Go, hurry!

47
00:03:03,182 --> 00:03:04,100
[gunshots]

48
00:03:04,183 --> 00:03:06,603
Aah!

49
00:03:07,687 --> 00:03:08,646
Edong!

50
00:03:08,730 --> 00:03:12,317
[suspenseful music playing]

51
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:14,277
- [Edong grunts]
- [gunshots]

52
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:15,486
[Edong groans]

53
00:03:16,362 --> 00:03:17,196
[groans]

54
00:03:18,531 --> 00:03:22,118
[suspenseful music continues]

55
00:03:25,121 --> 00:03:26,414
[blow lands]

56
00:03:26,497 --> 00:03:27,290
[body thuds]

57
00:03:29,208 --> 00:03:33,296
[music becomes ominous]

58
00:03:47,518 --> 00:03:48,895
[phone buzzing]

59
00:03:50,271 --> 00:03:53,274
- Sir, Santiago got away.
- [siren blaring]

60
00:03:53,358 --> 00:03:54,734
Son of a bitch!

61
00:03:54,817 --> 00:03:55,818
Idiots!

62
00:03:55,902 --> 00:03:57,570
<i>How did that happen?</i>

63
00:03:57,654 --> 00:03:59,030
<i>There were four of you</i>

64
00:03:59,113 --> 00:04:00,657
and Santiago was alone.

65
00:04:00,740 --> 00:04:01,991
He slipped past you?

66
00:04:02,075 --> 00:04:03,284
Sir, there was a commotion.

67
00:04:03,368 --> 00:04:05,787
Another group arrived,
and they were also after Edong.

68
00:04:06,204 --> 00:04:09,207
Then that's even more
reason to find and kill Santiago.

69
00:04:09,290 --> 00:04:11,876
<i>I don't know who those bastards are,</i>

70
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:15,922
but they could use
Santiago to drag us down.

71
00:04:16,005 --> 00:04:17,966
[music fades]

72
00:04:18,049 --> 00:04:18,925
[doorknob clicks]

73
00:04:19,634 --> 00:04:21,177
Please come in, ma'am.

74
00:04:21,261 --> 00:04:22,262
[Erica] Thank you.

75
00:04:26,516 --> 00:04:27,809
[Rose] Please have a seat.

76
00:04:34,774 --> 00:04:39,070
[pensive music playing]

77
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:56,004
[pensive music continues]

78
00:05:08,057 --> 00:05:09,267
Mel.

79
00:05:09,350 --> 00:05:12,979
[pensive music continues]

80
00:05:13,062 --> 00:05:14,480
[Erica] <i>Mel! </i>[breathing heavily]

81
00:05:14,564 --> 00:05:15,648
<i>Mel!</i>

82
00:05:15,732 --> 00:05:16,816
<i>It's Mel!</i>

83
00:05:16,899 --> 00:05:17,775
[breathing heavily]

84
00:05:17,859 --> 00:05:19,986
<i>It's Mel. Let go of me!</i>

85
00:05:23,239 --> 00:05:24,365
You're okay.

86
00:05:24,907 --> 00:05:26,367
[chuckles]

87
00:05:26,451 --> 00:05:30,079
I heard you had a bit of
excitement at your place, but look…

88
00:05:30,788 --> 00:05:31,956
It's still intact.

89
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:32,999
[exhales deeply]

90
00:05:33,082 --> 00:05:34,125
Oh god, Mel.

91
00:05:34,208 --> 00:05:37,754
Please stop it with that joke.
You're so morbid.

92
00:05:39,922 --> 00:05:40,923
Sorry.

93
00:05:42,258 --> 00:05:44,010
- [doorbell rings]
- [knocking on door]

94
00:05:44,093 --> 00:05:48,181
[pensive music continues]

95
00:05:48,264 --> 00:05:49,140
[doorknob clicks]

96
00:05:49,223 --> 00:05:50,475
[music fades]

97
00:05:50,558 --> 00:05:51,851
[Chloe] Hello, Aunt Alice.

98
00:05:51,934 --> 00:05:52,935
[Alice] Come in.

99
00:06:01,235 --> 00:06:02,820
Attorney Erica!

100
00:06:02,904 --> 00:06:03,863
You are the GOAT!

101
00:06:03,946 --> 00:06:06,324
You're my idol! I'm Chloe.

102
00:06:06,783 --> 00:06:09,327
Hi, Chloe. It's nice to meet you.

103
00:06:10,578 --> 00:06:15,208
[uneasy music playing]

104
00:06:28,346 --> 00:06:33,518
[uneasy music continues]

105
00:06:37,438 --> 00:06:40,483
[music becomes sinister]

106
00:06:40,566 --> 00:06:41,567
[coughs]

107
00:06:44,320 --> 00:06:45,321
Aah.

108
00:06:45,404 --> 00:06:48,908
[sinister music continues]

109
00:06:51,744 --> 00:06:52,745
[grunts]

110
00:06:56,249 --> 00:06:57,250
[winces]

111
00:07:07,176 --> 00:07:09,428
[sinister music fades]

112
00:07:12,098 --> 00:07:16,477
[foreboding music playing]

113
00:07:23,818 --> 00:07:24,861
- [grunts]
- [groans]

114
00:07:24,944 --> 00:07:26,821
- Dad!
- [Lucas groans]

115
00:07:30,199 --> 00:07:31,492
[Lucas coughing]

116
00:07:32,368 --> 00:07:36,247
I could easily tell my men to finish you.

117
00:07:36,330 --> 00:07:38,833
But you're here…

118
00:07:39,667 --> 00:07:41,294
and still breathing!

119
00:07:42,378 --> 00:07:45,590
They even drove your car to get here.

120
00:07:47,216 --> 00:07:50,970
You should be in
a church having your last rites.

121
00:07:51,053 --> 00:07:53,514
I said I would handle my brother!

122
00:07:53,598 --> 00:07:56,559
You think I have time
for your sibling problems?

123
00:07:57,310 --> 00:07:59,604
My business is at stake here!

124
00:07:59,687 --> 00:08:02,064
I've contributed a lot to your syndicate!

125
00:08:02,148 --> 00:08:03,107
Hey!

126
00:08:03,191 --> 00:08:04,567
Without me,

127
00:08:04,650 --> 00:08:09,530
you would still be
begging people to support

128
00:08:09,614 --> 00:08:11,491
whatever businesses you wanted.

129
00:08:12,158 --> 00:08:14,744
So don't act so arrogant.

130
00:08:15,244 --> 00:08:17,788
Every business you run

131
00:08:17,872 --> 00:08:20,625
is just a front for my group's money!

132
00:08:21,292 --> 00:08:24,212
Then take all
your money out of my business.

133
00:08:24,295 --> 00:08:28,799
[foreboding music continues]

134
00:08:31,802 --> 00:08:34,055
You think you can live without me?

135
00:08:35,515 --> 00:08:36,682
I can.

136
00:08:36,766 --> 00:08:41,979
- [music becomes dramatic]
- [laughing]

137
00:08:44,273 --> 00:08:48,069
You are tied to this
group for as long as I want.

138
00:08:49,070 --> 00:08:50,321
Try to break free.

139
00:08:51,239 --> 00:08:52,657
You'll see…

140
00:08:53,658 --> 00:08:57,787
you and your brother
will end up in the same grave!

141
00:09:02,041 --> 00:09:06,546
[dramatic music continues]

142
00:09:09,298 --> 00:09:10,841
<i>- "Bana?"</i>
- [music fades]

143
00:09:10,925 --> 00:09:13,511
I remembered she once wrote,

144
00:09:13,594 --> 00:09:15,888
"My <i>Bana,</i> I love you."

145
00:09:17,265 --> 00:09:19,225
I never heard that term from Louisa.

146
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:22,270
And you think that was her boyfriend?

147
00:09:23,646 --> 00:09:26,232
I mean, it was obviously a love note.

148
00:09:28,442 --> 00:09:30,236
Remember when we were asking her

149
00:09:30,319 --> 00:09:32,572
about that "L" initial at
the back of her watch?

150
00:09:33,406 --> 00:09:35,992
She didn't want
to tell us who gave it to her.

151
00:09:36,534 --> 00:09:39,537
And we were all
thinking it was from her boyfriend.

152
00:09:41,414 --> 00:09:42,999
Do you think it's the same person?

153
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:48,588
[pensive music playing]

154
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:55,678
Dude! Dude, why did you say that?

155
00:09:55,761 --> 00:09:57,054
Why?

156
00:09:57,138 --> 00:09:59,056
You know Dad will get mad!

157
00:10:00,850 --> 00:10:01,892
[sighs]

158
00:10:01,976 --> 00:10:04,353
Okay, okay, okay.
I will do my best to pacify him.

159
00:10:04,437 --> 00:10:06,105
But Lucas, you have to hear me out.

160
00:10:07,189 --> 00:10:09,108
- You need to lay low--
- Lay low?

161
00:10:09,817 --> 00:10:12,445
You know your father will
do everything to kill my brother!

162
00:10:13,654 --> 00:10:15,531
I'll find my brother and I don't care

163
00:10:15,615 --> 00:10:17,825
what Laurence Kyo does to me!

164
00:10:18,618 --> 00:10:19,619
Dude…

165
00:10:20,995 --> 00:10:21,996
What the…

166
00:10:22,913 --> 00:10:23,831
Lucas--

167
00:10:23,914 --> 00:10:28,419
[suspenseful music playing]

168
00:10:32,131 --> 00:10:34,884
- Nanny Rose, I need to pee-pee.
- [music fades]

169
00:10:34,967 --> 00:10:35,968
Alright, come on.

170
00:10:37,386 --> 00:10:39,180
- Stay here, Chloe.
- Okay.

171
00:10:45,728 --> 00:10:49,315
But didn't we think that
the "L" stands for Louisa?

172
00:10:50,524 --> 00:10:53,903
She probably just
bought the watch for herself.

173
00:10:53,986 --> 00:10:57,156
And maybe she was only
messing with us that she had a boyfriend

174
00:10:57,239 --> 00:10:58,908
because she loved teasing us, right?

175
00:10:58,991 --> 00:11:00,493
I am convinced she had a boyfriend--

176
00:11:00,576 --> 00:11:01,911
But if she really had a boyfriend

177
00:11:01,994 --> 00:11:03,579
why did she keep it a secret from us?

178
00:11:03,663 --> 00:11:04,288
Yeah.

179
00:11:05,706 --> 00:11:07,958
[Marco] Maybe he was older.

180
00:11:08,668 --> 00:11:09,669
Or maybe he was married.

181
00:11:11,253 --> 00:11:15,299
[pensive music playing]

182
00:11:15,383 --> 00:11:19,136
All I know is Louisa wanted
to leave Amurao because of him.

183
00:11:19,678 --> 00:11:22,223
So we need to find out his identity.

184
00:11:22,306 --> 00:11:25,810
Why? Do you think he has something to do
with what happened to Louisa?

185
00:11:26,727 --> 00:11:30,606
[pensive music continues]

186
00:11:30,689 --> 00:11:33,818
Why are we looking for
people who might not even be real?

187
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:36,779
We all know what happened, right?

188
00:11:37,363 --> 00:11:39,615
Edong killed Louisa.

189
00:11:39,949 --> 00:11:42,326
Because if he didn't,
why would he break out of jail

190
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:43,869
to find us and take revenge?

191
00:11:43,953 --> 00:11:47,581
Because he is furious at us
for locking him up when he was innocent.

192
00:11:48,499 --> 00:11:50,709
But you would never admit that!

193
00:11:50,793 --> 00:11:55,005
[tense music playing]

194
00:12:10,020 --> 00:12:11,856
[music fades]

195
00:12:26,537 --> 00:12:27,663
[exhales sharply]

196
00:12:29,373 --> 00:12:30,624
[coughs]

197
00:12:32,626 --> 00:12:38,215
[gentle music playing]

198
00:12:43,888 --> 00:12:45,347
[chuckles]

199
00:12:45,431 --> 00:12:47,558
She better thank me tomorrow.

200
00:12:48,350 --> 00:12:50,561
[imitates Chloe]
"What? You couldn't do it, bro?"

201
00:12:51,353 --> 00:12:53,314
"You're so cringe, bro."

202
00:12:54,398 --> 00:12:57,234
Mama and Papa have
been end game since high school!

203
00:12:59,653 --> 00:13:00,946
You're really something, aren't you?!

204
00:13:01,572 --> 00:13:05,075
You're really taking the side of
the serial killer who wants to kill us?!

205
00:13:05,493 --> 00:13:09,121
Ah Beth, I think that's unfair. I mean…

206
00:13:10,414 --> 00:13:13,334
Erica's been helping us
ever since Edong became a threat to us.

207
00:13:13,417 --> 00:13:16,170
No! I'm sorry. I have to agree with Beth.

208
00:13:16,754 --> 00:13:19,006
The situation is complicated enough.

209
00:13:19,089 --> 00:13:22,384
Why do we have to dig up
the past for questions and theories?

210
00:13:22,468 --> 00:13:24,220
As far as we and
the authorities are concerned,

211
00:13:24,303 --> 00:13:26,096
all the questions have been answered.

212
00:13:26,180 --> 00:13:28,682
Why don't we ask your friend Lucas?

213
00:13:30,518 --> 00:13:32,102
Ask him about Esther.

214
00:13:33,771 --> 00:13:35,648
He knows Esther lied

215
00:13:35,731 --> 00:13:38,526
that she saw Edong
the night Louisa was killed!

216
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:41,320
Esther thought Edong would report her

217
00:13:41,403 --> 00:13:43,697
for stealing the alumni funds

218
00:13:45,115 --> 00:13:48,994
But she had Edong
imprisoned so she could escape her debt!

219
00:13:49,078 --> 00:13:50,162
[Beth] And what?!

220
00:13:50,246 --> 00:13:52,706
We're going to believe
what Edong and Lucas said?

221
00:13:52,790 --> 00:13:54,458
Of course, they'll say that!

222
00:13:54,542 --> 00:13:55,584
Oh?

223
00:13:55,668 --> 00:13:57,920
A few weeks ago,
you were defending Lucas, weren't you?

224
00:13:58,712 --> 00:14:01,507
You said he wouldn't get involved
in his brother's revenge.

225
00:14:01,590 --> 00:14:03,634
Now we're not going
to believe him anymore?

226
00:14:05,302 --> 00:14:06,262
And you, Beth!

227
00:14:06,345 --> 00:14:09,181
You said it was impossible
for Edong to have killed Celestino.

228
00:14:09,265 --> 00:14:11,392
That it was impossible
for him to take revenge on us.

229
00:14:11,475 --> 00:14:13,894
Well now, it's clear
to us that you were wrong.

230
00:14:14,478 --> 00:14:17,648
Why is it so hard for you to accept
that you might be wrong again?

231
00:14:20,276 --> 00:14:25,406
[unsettling music playing]

232
00:14:30,077 --> 00:14:31,036
[Rose] Chloe!

233
00:14:33,581 --> 00:14:34,999
What would you like to drink?

234
00:14:35,082 --> 00:14:36,834
Juice or soft drink?

235
00:14:38,127 --> 00:14:40,004
[Chloe] Anything is fine, Miss Rose.

236
00:14:43,591 --> 00:14:46,051
[Alice sighs heavily]

237
00:14:46,135 --> 00:14:48,762
[Rose] Ma'am,
will she be having dinner here?

238
00:14:48,846 --> 00:14:51,390
- I'll start serving--
- No, please don't bother.

239
00:14:51,473 --> 00:14:55,060
[unsettling music playing]

240
00:14:55,978 --> 00:14:57,479
[Seth] Car.

241
00:14:59,189 --> 00:15:00,190
[Alice] Oh--

242
00:15:02,610 --> 00:15:05,654
Um, baby, we're going to have
dinner in a bit. Start packing away.

243
00:15:05,738 --> 00:15:06,739
- Okay?
- Okay.

244
00:15:09,909 --> 00:15:15,164
[unsettling music continues]

245
00:15:26,884 --> 00:15:28,677
[Joshua] Chloe will love this.

246
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:44,234
[Liezel] Joshua, come here! Hurry!

247
00:15:45,319 --> 00:15:47,071
- [ominous music sting]
- [music ends]

248
00:15:50,366 --> 00:15:51,408
[door bangs]

249
00:15:51,492 --> 00:15:54,453
- [Liezel] He's coming! [chuckles]
- [Angelo] He's excited!

250
00:15:54,536 --> 00:15:55,496
Papa!

251
00:15:56,205 --> 00:15:58,248
Joshua! My son!

252
00:15:58,332 --> 00:16:00,042
[hearty laughter] Let me see you!

253
00:16:00,125 --> 00:16:03,963
Wow! You're so grown up! [smooches]

254
00:16:04,046 --> 00:16:06,048
You look exactly like your daddy!

255
00:16:06,131 --> 00:16:07,508
[hearty laughter]

256
00:16:07,591 --> 00:16:13,305
[light-hearted music playing]

257
00:16:21,355 --> 00:16:23,148
[music fades]

258
00:16:25,109 --> 00:16:29,238
[ominous music playing]

259
00:16:33,867 --> 00:16:35,869
"MY BANA, I LOVE YOU."

260
00:16:36,745 --> 00:16:38,372
[Erica] Take care.

261
00:16:38,455 --> 00:16:41,333
For now,
don't accept any suspicious packages.

262
00:16:41,417 --> 00:16:42,418
